ractModule`, bindings, injection points, providers, scopes, and method interceptors. Avoid importing old unprefixed internal classes like `com.google.inject.internal.util.MapMaker` or `com.google.inject.internal.cglib.proxy.MethodProxy`; in this artifact many shaded internals are stored with `$`-prefixed class names and direct internal imports caused the javac failure.\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"Tests that only cover simple field/constructor injection may pass without `--add-opens`, but they will miss important dynamic proxy and interceptor behavior.\",\n    \"Optional `org.slf4j:slf4j-api` is declared by the artifact but is not needed for normal meaningful Guice coverage unless tests intentionally target logging-specific behavior.\",\n    \"Direct tests of relocated internal implementation classes are brittle across sisu-guice versions and can fail at javac before reaching metadata validation.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_01ff196f38903a64016a41dc791208819785ca15d67359939f\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1937, "output": 662, "cacheRead": 19968, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 22567, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1782701171468, "responseId": "resp_01ff196f38903a64016a41dc73eaec819789d138ae8cb21804"}}
